                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><a href="https://demetriamartinez.net/"><strong>Demetria Martinez</strong></a> is a poet, writer, and activist. Her books, among others, include the novels&nbsp;<em>Mother Tongue</em> (Ballantine) and <em>The&nbsp;Block Captain’s Daughter</em> (University of Oklahoma Press); a book of essays,&nbsp;<em>Confessions of a Berlitz-Tape Chicana</em> (University of Oklahoma Press); and an ebook about immigration reform,&nbsp;<em>Let Them Work</em>, co-authored with Fred Harris, former Oklahoma state senator. She has been a recipient of the Luis Leal Award for Distinction in Chicano/Latino Literature; an American Book Award; and an International Latino Book Award.&nbsp;Her most recent book, coauthored with Susan Sherman, is <em>Poetry in Dangerous Times: Two Women, Two Worlds</em>.</p>
